headlines.description: — Collin Sexton scored 30 points and Darius Garland added 25 as the Cleveland Cavaliers never trailed in a 121-105 win over the Chicago Bulls on Wednesday night, snapping a five-game home losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Collin Sexton scores 30 points, Cavs beat Bulls 121-105

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Indiana Pacers

headlines.description: — With seven men out, the Indiana Pacers came up big by playing small ball Wednesday night, running away from the reeling Oklahoma City Thunder 122-116.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers' small ball comes up big in 122-116 win over Thunder

headlines.description: — Chris Paul scored 28 points, Devin Booker had 19 and Mikal Bridges 18 to lead the Phoenix Suns to a 116-113 victory over the Philadelphia 76ers on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Paul, Booker lead Suns past undermanned 76ers, 116-113

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry had his first rough night in a month, and Bradley Beal rallied Washington in the fourth quarter for its season-best sixth straight victory, 118-114 over the Golden State Warriors on Wednesday night in the first Wizards home game with...
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry finally goes cold, Beal rallies Wizards past Warriors

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam had 27 points and nine rebounds, OG Anunoby scored 25 points and the Toronto Raptors seized control in the third quarter in a 114-103 victory over the Brooklyn Nets on Wednesday night, extending their winning streak to four games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Raptors ride strong 3rd quarter to 114-103 win over Nets

events.name: Atlanta Hawks at New York Knicks

headlines.description: - Julius Randle had 40 points and 10 rebounds to lead New York to a 137-127 overtime victory over the Atlanta Hawks on Wednesday night, the Knicks' NBA-best eighth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Randle sends Knicks past Hawks 137-127 in OT for 8th in row

headlines.description: — Jordan Clarkson scored 22 points, Joe Ingles had 21 and the NBA-leading Utah Jazz beat the Houston Rockets 112-89 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clarkson scores 22 points, NBA-leading Jazz beat Rockets

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 30 points and 10 rebounds, Kristaps Porzingis added 19 points and seven boards and the Dallas Mavericks beat the Detroit Pistons 127-117 on Wednesday night to stop a four-game home losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic, Mavs beat Pistons 127-117 to stop 4-game home skid

events.name: Miami Heat at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Bam Adebayo scored 23 points while Jimmy Butler had 18 points and 11 assists to help the Miami Heat beat the San Antonio Spurs 107-87 on Wednesday night for their third straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Adebayo, Butler lead Heat by Spurs for third straight win

headlines.description: — Luke Kennard scored a season-high 28 points and the short-handed Los Angeles Clippers rallied from an 18-point, first-quarter deficit to beat the Memphis Grizzlies 117-105 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers recover after poor start, beat Grizzlies 117-105

events.name: Denver Nuggets at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic scored 25 points and made three key free throws down the stretch to give the Denver Nuggets a 106-105 victory over the Portland trail Blazers on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic scores 25, Denver beats Portland for 4th straight win

headlines.description: — Buddy Hield scored 29 points, including a 3-pointer with 8.8 seconds remaining, lifting the Sacramento Kings to a 128-125 win over the Minnesota Timberwolves on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hield's late 3 lifts Kings past Timberwolves 128-125
